10000037.desc: The secretary at Yuehai Pavilion. The blood of the qilin, an illuminated beast, flows within her veins.

10000025.desc: A young man carrying a longsword who is frequently seen at book booths. He has a chivalrous heart and yearns for justice and fairness for all.

10000091.desc: The current President of Spina di Rosula, who is lovely, dutiful, and a great boss.

10000007-7.desc: A traveler from another world who had their only kin taken away, forcing them to embark on a journey to find The Seven.

10000092.desc: Guard of the Sword and Strongbox Secure Transport Agency, and the head of the "Mighty Mythical Beasts" Wushou troupe.

10000032.desc: A good-natured adventurer from Mondstadt who's unfortunately extremely unlucky.

10000050.desc: The Kamisato Clan's housekeeper. A well-known "fixer" in Inazuma.

10000085.desc: A reserved young man who is well-versed in diving. Beneath his distant, icy demeanor lies a pure heart bereft of all flaws.

10000083.desc: A magic assistant of few words, her emotions are as inscrutable as any cat's.

10000065.desc: The capable and reliable Arataki Gang deputy leader. Please note: capable and reliable are not appellations for the "Arataki Gang," but for their deputy leader in specific.

10000002.desc: Daughter of the Yashiro Commission's Kamisato Clan. Dignified and elegant, as well as wise and strong.

10000015.desc: An accomplished swordsman and a strategic thinker in the Knights of Favonius, rumored to hail from beyond Mondstadt.

10000042.desc: The Yuheng of the Liyue Qixing. Keqing has much to say about Rex Lapis's unilateral approach to policymaking in Liyue — but in truth, gods admire skeptics such as her quite a lot.

10000043.desc: An alchemist filled with curiosity about all things. She researches bio-alchemy.

10000100.desc: A young warrior of the Nanatzcayan, given the Ancient Name of "Uthabiti." Kind-hearted and insatiably persistent, she grows stronger and more capable with each setback she faces.

10000007-4.desc: A traveler from another world who had their only kin taken away, forcing them to embark on a journey to find The Seven.

10000007-6.desc: A traveler from another world who had their only kin taken away, forcing them to embark on a journey to find The Seven.

10000095.desc: A Melusine and the Fortress of Meropide's head nurse. She cares equally for every convict locked in the undersea prison.

10000033.desc: No. 11 of The Harbingers, also known as "Childe." His name is highly feared on the battlefield.

10000073.desc: A caged bird secluded within the confines of the Sanctuary of Surasthana who can only see the world in her dreams.

10000071.desc: The General Mahamatra in charge of supervising the researchers of the Akademiya. It is said that when he gets down to work, the General Mahamatra is even more efficient than the "Great Vayuvyastra" made by the Kshahrewar.

10000006.desc: The languid but knowledgeable Librarian of the Knights of Favonius, deemed by Sumeru Akademiya to be their most distinguished graduate in the past two centuries.

10000007-3.desc: A traveler from another world who had their only kin taken away, forcing them to embark on a journey to find The Seven.

10000088.desc: Indefatigable reporter of The Steambird, constantly on the hunt for the "truth."

10000094.desc: The owner of Chioriya Boutique. A tailor renowned throughout Fontaine.

10000044.desc: Liyue's sole rock 'n' roll musician. She rebels against ossified prejudices using her music and passionate singing.

10000075.desc: A wayfaring figure whose identity is a mystery. He dresses like a mountain ascetic, but he certainly does not act the part.

10000052.desc: Her Excellency, the Almighty Narukami Ogosho, who promised the people of Inazuma an unchanging Eternity.

10000102.desc: A well-known guide in Natlan who owns a watersports shop, and expert in all forms of wave-chasing.

10000021.desc: Always energetic and full of life, Amber's the best — albeit only — Outrider of the Knights of Favonius.

10000054.desc: The Divine Priestess of Watatsumi Island. All of the island's affairs are at this young lady's fingertips.

10000058.desc: Lady Guuji of the Grand Narukami Shrine. Also serves as the editor-in-chief of Yae Publishing House. Unimaginable intelligence and cunning are hidden under her beautiful appearance.

10000046.desc: The 77th Director of the Wangsheng Funeral Parlor. She took over the business at a rather young age.

10000034.desc: A maid who faithfully serves the Knights of Favonius. She dreams of joining their ranks someday.

10000093.desc: One of the Mighty and Illuminated Adepti of Jueyun, known as "Cloud Retainer." Expert in all kinds of mechanical contraptions, her heart now turns towards the affairs of the mortal world, through which she walks under the name "Xianyun."

10000007-8.desc: A traveler from another world who had their only kin taken away, forcing them to embark on a journey to find The Seven.

10000096.desc: "The Knave," Fourth of the Fatui Harbingers. A poised, ruthless diplomat. To the children in the House of the Hearth, she is their feared yet dependable "Father."

10000082.desc: The owner of Bubu Pharmacy, who is rarely seen without the white snake named Changsheng. His medicinal knowledge is encyclopedic, and his personal intrigues subtle.

10000036.desc: A young exorcist from a family of exorcists. He does everything he can to suppress his abundance of yang energy.

10000049.desc: Owner of Naganohara Fireworks. Known as the "Queen of the Summer Festival," she excels in her craft of creating fireworks that symbolize people's hopes and dreams.

10000089.desc: The absolute focus of the stage of judgment, until the final applause sounds.

10000051.desc: The Spindrift Knight, a scion of the old aristocracy, and the Captain of the Knights of Favonius Reconnaissance Company. The reason for which a descendant of the ancient nobles might join the Knights remains a great mystery in Mondstadt to this very day.

10000064.desc: A renowned Liyue opera singer who is skilled in both playwriting and singing. Her style is one-of-a-kind, exquisite and delicate, much like the person herself.

10000076.desc: A researcher from "one hundred years ago." She enjoys self-identifying as everyone's senior, and has significant knowledge of ancient scripts and machines of all kinds.

10000063.desc: An adepti disciple with a most unusual air about her. Having spent much time cultivating in isolation in Liyue's mountains, she has become every bit as cool and distant as the adepti themselves.

10000003.desc: The righteous and rigorous Dandelion Knight, and Acting Grand Master of Mondstadt's Knights of Favonius.

10000060.desc: A mysterious person who claims to work for the Ministry of Civil Affairs, but is a "non-entity" on the Ministry of Civil Affairs' list.

10000067.desc: A trainee ranger active in Avidya Forest. Behind her enthusiastic words and actions hides a slightly introverted personality.

10000027.desc: The Tianquan of the Liyue Qixing. Her wealth is unsurpassed in all of Teyvat.

10000029.desc: An explosives expert and a regular at the Knights of Favonius's confinement room. Also known as Fleeing Sunlight.

10000005-6.desc: A traveler from another world who had their only kin taken away, forcing them to embark on a journey to find The Seven.

10000057.desc: The first and greatest head of the Arataki Gang, famed throughout Inazuma City's Hanamizaka... Wait, what? You've never heard of them? Are you trying to be funny here?

10000066.desc: The young but highly accomplished head of the Yashiro Commission's Kamisato Clan. Cultured and polite, he is a man of many ways and means.

10000077.desc: Streetward Rambler's youngest disciple. A gentle and caring "little adult."

10000038.desc: A genius known as the Kreideprinz, he is the Chief Alchemist and Captain of the Investigation Team of the Knights of Favonius.

10000098.desc: An undefeated Champion Duelist. Sword in hand, she defends justice in the Court of Fontaine.

10000101.desc: A Huitztlan Saurian Hunter skilled at counting costs.

10000005-3.desc: A traveler from another world who had their only kin taken away, forcing them to embark on a journey to find The Seven.

10000074.desc: A Rtawahist student who specializes in Theoretical Astrology. Heavily prone to somnambulism and locked in a grinding war with sleep deprivation, the problem of restful slumber is a most troubling one to her.

10000014.desc: Every citizen of Mondstadt adores Barbara. She learned the word "idol" from a magazine.

10000024.desc: Captain of her crew, The Crux. She's quite an unbound and forthright woman.

10000072.desc: A descendant of King Deshret with an amber left eye. The defender of Aaru Village.

10000099.desc: A Fontainian perfumer, one who bottles secrets.

10000061.desc: A courier for Komaniya Express, a delivery company in Inazuma. A nekomata who loves her job and human society.

10000005-7.desc: A traveler from another world who had their only kin taken away, forcing them to embark on a journey to find The Seven.

10000020.desc: A boy who lives among the wolves in Wolvendom of Mondstadt, away from human civilization. As agile as lightning.

10000048.desc: A well-known legal adviser active in Liyue Harbor. A brilliant young lady in whose veins runs the blood of an illuminated beast.

10000068.desc: An elusive merchant who has a fondness for glittering Mora.

10000022.desc: One of the many bards of Mondstadt, who freely wanders the city's streets and alleys.

10000080.desc: A young knight born to an ordinary family. He serves as a Front-Line Surveyor in his Company. He is a low-key and cautious character.

10000055.desc: The great general of Watatsumi Island's forces. He is deeply trusted by his subordinates.

10000026.desc: A yaksha adeptus who defends Liyue. Also heralded as the "Conqueror of Demons" and "Vigilant Yaksha."

10000081.desc: A renowned architect from Sumeru who perhaps cares a bit too much about too many things. He is an aesthete troubled by reality.

10000078.desc: The current scribe of the Sumeru Akademiya, a man endowed with extraordinary intelligence and talent. He lives free — free from the searching eyes of ordinary people, anyway.

10000090.desc: The captain of the Special Security and Surveillance Patrol, who wears justice as an ever-present seal upon her heart. Her musket shall only ever point at the guilty.

10000097.desc: The Temple of Silence's heir. Burdened with secrets, he comes from the sands.

10000053.desc: A pint-sized ninja attached to the Shuumatsuban, who always seems sleep-deprived.

10000070.desc: The star of the Zubayr Theater. She is full of warmth and innocence, and her dances are lively and elegant.

10000031.desc: A mysterious girl who calls herself "Prinzessin der Verurteilung" and travels with a night raven named Oz.

10000045.desc: A sister of the church, though you wouldn't know it if it weren't for her attire. Known for her sharp, cold words and manner, she often works alone.

10000079.desc: A member of the Eremites, a mercenary organization that roams the sands of Sumeru. Valiant and powerful, she enjoys great fame amongst her fellow Eremites.

10000035.desc: An apprentice and herb gatherer at Bubu Pharmacy. An undead with a bone-white complexion, she seldom has much in the way of words or emotion.

10000047.desc: A wandering samurai from Inazuma who is currently with Liyue's Crux Fleet. A gentle and carefree soul whose heart hides a great many burdens from the past.

10000086.desc: Duke of the Fortress of Meropide, Lord Incognito of the murky depths.

10000005-4.desc: A traveler from another world who had their only kin taken away, forcing them to embark on a journey to find The Seven.

10000087.desc: The Chief Justice of Fontaine, known as the Iudex, is renowned for his unassailable impartiality.

10000023.desc: A renowned chef from Liyue. She's extremely passionate about cooking and excels at making her signature hot and spicy dishes.

10000041.desc: A mysterious young astrologer who proclaims herself to be "Astrologist Mona Megistus," and who possesses abilities to match the title. Erudite, but prideful.

10000005-8.desc: A traveler from another world who had their only kin taken away, forcing them to embark on a journey to find The Seven.

10000056.desc: A general of the Tenryou Commission. Bold, decisive, and skilled in battle.

10000039.desc: A young lady who has inherited trace amounts of non-human blood. She is the incredibly popular bartender of the Cat's Tail tavern.

10000062.desc: Formerly an outcast, now a hunter of unparalleled skill. Ready to do the right thing at any time.

10000069.desc: A young researcher well-versed in botany who currently serves as a Forest Watcher in Avidya Forest. He is a straight shooter with a warm heart — and a dab hand at guiding even the dullest of pupils.

10000016.desc: The tycoon of a winery empire in Mondstadt, unmatched in every possible way.

10000103.desc: A Name Engraver of the Nanatzcayan, she is especially skilled at finding a good balance between the heavy responsibilities of her job and living well.

10000059.desc: A young prodigy detective from the Tenryou Commission. His senses are sharp and his thoughts are clear.

10000084.desc: A famed Fontainian magician who possesses great stage presence as well as gift of the gab. Audiences are enthralled by his exquisite skills, and they hang on to his every clever word.

10000030.desc: A mysterious expert contracted by the Wangsheng Funeral Parlor. Extremely knowledgeable in all things.
